segment.source: Importing results is the process of copying results from other locations to the default results library.
segment.target: Importing results is the process of copying results from other locations to the default results library.

segment.source: The results that you want to import can be on the local computer, a network share, or removable media.
segment.target: The results that you want to import can be on the local computer, a network share, or removable media.

segment.source: This topic describes how to copy results to the default results library by using Windows Assessment Console.
segment.target: This topic describes how to copy results to the default results library by using Windows Assessment Console.

segment.source: To import results
segment.target: To import results

segment.source: Click Options, and then click Import Results.
segment.target: Click Options, and then click Import Results.

segment.source: In the Import Results dialog box, click Browse to locate the results that you want to import from the local computer, a network share, or removable media.
segment.target: In the Import Results dialog box, click Browse to locate the results that you want to import from the local computer, a network share, or removable media.

segment.source: Locate the folder that contains the results that you want, click the folder, and then click Select Folder.
segment.target: Locate the folder that contains the results that you want, click the folder, and then click Select Folder.

segment.source: The path of that folder appears in the Import from box in the Import Results dialog box.
segment.target: The path of that folder appears in the Import from box in the Import Results dialog box.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: The import copies the selected folder.
segment.target: The import copies the selected folder.

segment.source: It doesn't move and delete items from the source folder.
segment.target: It doesn't move and delete items from the source folder.

segment.source: Click Next.
segment.target: Click Next.

segment.source: The Windows Assessment Console imports the selected results into the default results library on the local computer.
segment.target: The Windows Assessment Console imports the selected results into the default results library on the local computer.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: The Windows Assessment Console can import results only from locations that don't contribute to the assessment results library.
segment.target: The Windows Assessment Console can import results only from locations that don't contribute to the assessment results library.

segment.source: If you attempt to import results from any folder that's listed in the assessments results library locations, you'll receive an error message.
segment.target: If you attempt to import results from any folder that's listed in the assessments results library locations, you'll receive an error message.
